<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-16T13:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-16T13:40:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/2255: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herod</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-16T14:00:00-04:40"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. Your 1, January 7, 2 p.m. Your instruction number 429 received to-day
                            and I have sent Acting Military Governor enclosure in the manner
                            directed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herod</hi></signed></closer>
